# Kenku Controller
This is an arduino sketch and a python script to control [Kenku FM](https://www.kenku.fm/) from hardware, for tabletop RPG. 

## Usage
Firstly you need to install Kenku FM from [here](https://www.kenku.fm/). Set up some playlists and soundboards. Enable the kenku remote (under the connect to discord link).

Flash the keypad_streamdeck.ino sketch to your arduino. 

Run the python script. 

## Configuration
The config.yaml.sample file provides an example configuration

## How it works
The arduino pings the serial port every 10 seconds. This response is aknowledged by the python script.

It also sends commands which are interpreted by the python script, which accesses appropriate 